news.title: AAIJI Group acquires 50 acres land in Dholera for Rs 150 crore
news.para: AAIJI Group plans to develop 3BHK villas, plots and retail spaces. Till date, the company has invested over Rs 100 crore in five projects in Dholera.

news.title: IBC may introduce voluntary group insolvency mechanism soon
news.para: The framework will be a part of Insolvency & Bankruptcy Code (IBC) amendments that the corporate affairs ministry could introduce in the winter session of Parliament, likely in December, they said

news.title: SC allows demolition of 41 illegal buildings in Agrawal Nagari, Mumbai
news.para: ​​The occupants, who were given a 24-hour notice by the VVMC on July 2, had sought relief from the Bombay High Court, which extended the eviction deadline to Oct 30 but refused to halt the demolition.

news.title: Gurugram: Chintels Paradiso's tower A declared unfit for living
news.para: The recent audit revealed significant structural deterioration in Tower A, primarily because of severe corrosion caused by high chloride content and poor-quality concrete — similar to issues found in the other towers. Tower A comprises 64 flats, 60 of which are occupied.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt directs administrations to form panels to implement new lift act
news.para: The legislation was approved by the state cabinet in July to control the rising accidents due to lifts and escalators in urban areas.

news.title: Lucknow: ED arrests Sai Construction and Builders' partner in loan fraud case
news.para: The ED initiated the probe against Tyagi based on an FIR registered by the CBI against M/s Sai Construction and Builders, Ghaziabad, its partners, and others under Sections IPC, 1860, and the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988, for alleged loan fraud.

news.title: Mumbai: ITAT grants full tax benefit for investment in two adjoining flats
news.para: Aggarwal had claimed a tax deduction of several crores under Section 54-F of Income Tax (I-T) Act, following his investment in two adjoining flats in a gated estate in Andheri.

news.title: Hyderabad: I-T department conducts searches at Anvitha Real Estate Group
news.para: Searches were also conducted at the offices of two directors, Atchuta Rao Boppana and Anup Boppana. Income tax officials inspected the registered office of Anvitha Infra Projects Private Limited in Raidurg, Gachibowli.

news.title: Prestige Estates sales bookings down 43% at Rs 4,022 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: ​​In a regulatory filing on Thursday, Prestige Estates informed that it recorded sales of Rs 4,022.6 crore during the July-September quarter against Rs 7,092.6 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: Over 60 buildings around Nagpur airport pose hurdles to flight path
news.para: RTI activist Abhay Kolarkar had asked six questions to the Airports Authority of India (AAI), which routed the answers through Mihan India Limited (MIL) — the airport operator at Nagpur.

news.title: Polycab India's net profit increases by 3.59% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Polycab India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 5,574.57 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 31.07 per cent from Rs 4,253.01 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nirala World buys 2.6 acre land in Greater Noida for Rs 180 crore
news.para: The parcel of land is located in the Greater Noida West sector 10 (Plot no C-6). The land was recently acquired through an auction by the Greater Noida Authority.

news.title: Havells India's net profit up 7.50% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Havells India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 4,632.20 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 17.19 per cent from Rs 3,952.81 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Not opposed to carbon trading, if used to improve value chain: Mahesh Ramanujam, CEO, GNFZ
news.para: Mahesh Ramanujam discusses his journey from USGBC to founding GNFZ, aiming for holistic decarbonization across various sectors. He highlights the need for transparency, government partnerships, and integrating sustainability with profitability.

news.title: Sunac China to raise $156 million in a bid to repay corporate debt
news.para: The Chinese property giant said it intends to utilize the net proceeds from the subscription primarily to support the long-term solutions for its onshore corporate bonds, the payments of which have been extended to 2024 end.

news.title: DPCC launches mandatory dust control portal for construction projects in Delhi
news.para: ​In line with the directives issued by the Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM) on December 20, 2021, the DPCC now mandates that all construction and demolition (C&D) projects occupying a plot area of 500 square metre or more must register on a newly-developed web portal, the pollution control authority said in a notice.

news.title: Hong Kong HC orders China's DaFa Properties to wind up
news.para: In February, the company received a winding-up petition from China Construction Bank (Asia) related to outstanding 12.375% senior notes due in 2022, totaling $360 million. The petition also included the company's unit, YinYi Holdings (Hong Kong).

news.title: Members of Karnataka state building and others protest, urging government to fulfil demands
news.para: Committee district general secretary, Yogesh Jappinamogaru, called on the govts to release the overdue monthly pensions that were withheld for the past two months.

news.title: Property transfers set to become easy in Pimpri Chinchwad with data integration
news.para: An official of the Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) said the residents would not require make a separate application to register their property with PCMC after the data intergration. "It will be done automatically once the data is updated with the IGR office," the official said.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body to demolish 16-storey building on development plan road
news.para: Ganesh Shimpi, assistant municipal commissioner of ward 4, where Jhalak falls, said, "After taking police security and other arrangements, we will demolish the building within a week."
